  "body": "Background https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/31762\nProposal  https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/34160 \nProposed actions for 1.5 https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/34160#issuecomment-254764348\n\nAt a high level: \n\nToday: \n- Partition \n  - nodecontroller \"deletes\" (sets deletionTimestamp)\n  - kubelet doesn't see this\n- Partition lasts for 5m\n  - nodecontroller \"hard deletes\" (kubectl delete --grace-period=0)\n- Partition recovers\n  - kubelet sees delete  \n  - kubelet sends sigkill\n\nIn 1.5:\n- Partition \n  - nodecontroller \"deletes\" (sets deletionTimestamp)\n  - kubelet doesn't see this\n- Partition lasts for 5m\n  - nothing happens\n- Parition recovers\n  - kubelet sees deletionTimestamp  \n  - kubelet sends sigterm, waits terminationGrace, sends sigkill\n  - kubelet \"hard deletes\" (kubectl delete --grace-period=0)\n\nIf you're responsible for a controller, think about the implications and bring up any objections.\n\nFor example, replica-set/tion controller treats deletionTimestamp as an effective delete, and eagerly creates a replacement. Creating a replacement daemon on a partitioned node isn't going to help anyway. And so on...\n\n@smarterclayton @foxish @erictune @janetkuo @kubernetes/sig-api-machinery @kubernetes/goog-control-plane  (sorry for the wide cc trying to get all controller owners)\n",
